From 7c87e9d263ae2704472eecc31310b10110f18d29 Mon Sep 17 00:00:00 2001
From: Claude <noreply@anthropic.com>
Date: Tue, 14 Jul 2026 16:40:49 +0000
Subject: [PATCH] Add Couch Delivery Sydney landing page

New page template (templates/page.couch-delivery-sydney.json) built entirely
from new, isolated theme blocks. No existing files were modified.

- Hero, intro, couch types grid, how-it-works, why-choose-us, pricing
  explainer, marketplace pickup, service areas, FAQ and final CTA are new
  reusable blocks (feature-grid and process-steps are shared across
  multiple sections to avoid duplicate CSS/markup).
- Reuses the existing Main Quote Form (blocks/ai_gen_block_8e89168.liquid,
  form id="main-quote") instead of creating a new form; hero and final CTA
  buttons link to #main-quote.
- Recent jobs section connects to the existing "recent_jobs" metaobject,
  filtered to couch/sofa jobs with a graceful fallback/hide.
- FAQ block renders FAQPage JSON-LD from the same nested block settings
  used for the visible accordion, so schema can't drift from content.
- Dedicated schema block adds only Service, WebPage and BreadcrumbList
  JSON-LD; no new Organization/LocalBusiness/AggregateRating schema, since
  Organization is already rendered sitewide by sections/header.liquid.
- Only one H1 (hero heading); all other headings are H2/H3.
- Internal links limited to pages confirmed to exist in the store
  (/pages/furniture-delivery-ryde).
